an class=title> OT: How to clean a cat (humor)</span><hr size=1> HOW TO BATHE A CAT<br>
&gt;<br>
&gt; 1. Thoroughly clean the toilet.<br>
&gt;<br>
&gt; 2. Add the required amount of shampoo to the toilet water and have<br>
&gt; both lids up.<br>
&gt;<br>
&gt; 3. Find the cat and soothe him while you carry him towards the<br>
&gt; bathroom.<br>
&gt;<br>
&gt; 4. In one smooth movement, put the cat in the toilet and close<br>
&gt; both lids. (You may need to stand on the lid so that he cannot<br>
&gt; escape.) The cat will self - agitate and make ample suds. Never<br>
&gt; mind the noises that come from your toilet, the cat is actually<br>
&gt; enjoying this.<br>
&gt;<br>
&gt; CAUTION: Do not get any part of your body too close to the edge,<br>
&gt; as his paws will be reaching out for anything they can find.<br>
&gt;<br>
&gt; 5. Flush the toilet three or four times. This provides a &quot;Power<br>
&gt; Wash&quot;and &quot;Rinse&quot;, which I have found to be quite effective.<br>
&gt;<br>
&gt; 6. Have someone open the door to the outside and ensure that there<br>
&gt; are no people between the toilet and the outside door.<br>
&gt;<br>
&gt; 7. Stand behind the toilet as far as you can, and quickly lift<br>
&gt; both lids.<br>
&gt;<br>
&gt; 8. The now clean cat will rocket out of the toilet, and run<br>
&gt; outside where he will dry himself.<br>
&gt;<br>
&gt; Sincerely,<br>
&gt; The Dog<br>
